                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The metric system is decimal-based and used worldwide (except in the US, Liberia, and Myanmar). Imperial units (used in the US) are based on historical measurements. 1 meter equals approximately 3.28084 feet, and 1 kilometer equals about 0.621371 miles.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <span>Are nautical miles different from regular miles?</span>
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes! A nautical mile is based on the circumference of the Earth and equals 1,852 meters (about 6,076 feet). A statute (regular) mile is 5,280 feet (1,609 meters). Nautical miles are used in maritime and aviation navigation.</p>
                    </div>
